										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>To say AI has grown in recent years would be the understatement of the century. A few years back, AI was largely a buzzword, with its use cases predominately limited to predictive analytics and chatbots. (This is grossly simplifying things, but you get the point.) Now, we‚Äôve reached a point where you can ask, ‚ÄúAre there ways to use AI for holiday marketing?‚Äù And, voila‚Äîthis question warrants an entire article. Written by a human, of course.</p>
<p>If you‚Äôre looking to answer said question and snag a few generative AI prompts while you‚Äôre at it, you‚Äôve come to the right place.</p>
<h3>Table of contents</h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="#how-ai-is-used-in-marketing">How is AI used in marketing?</a></li>
<li><a href="#how-to-use-ai-for-holiday-marketing">8 ways to use AI for holiday marketing</a></li>
<li><a href="#holiday-ai-prompts">15 holiday prompts for generative AI</a>
